<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8ff0605f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2665c"><num value="2665c">§ 2665c.</num><heading> Thomas R. Pickering Foreign Affairs Fellowship Program</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id8ff06060-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2665c/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There shall be in the Department a Thomas R. Pickering Foreign Affairs Fellowship Program.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id8ff06061-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2665c/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Purpose</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The program required by subsection (a) shall continue to provide financial assistance, mentoring, and professional development opportunities to graduate students who commit to pursuing careers in the Foreign Service of the United States.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id8ff06062-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2665c/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Administration</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The program required by subsection (a) shall be administered by the Department, consistent with existing law and regulations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id8ff06063-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/119/60/dE/tI/s5134">Pub. L. 119–60, div. E, title I, § 5134</ref>, <date date="2025-12-18">Dec. 18, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/1568">139 Stat. 1568</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8ff06064-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id8ff06065-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="definitions" id="id8ff06066-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Definitions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">For definition of “Department” as used in this section, see <ref href="/us/pl/119/60/s5002">section 5002 of Pub. L. 119–60</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s2651">section 2651 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
